===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|abod|lang=enm}}, {{term|abad|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{recons|abad|ābād|lang=ang}}, related to {{term|abidan|ābīdan|to abide|lang=ang}}; see ''[[abide]]''. Cognate with Scots {{term|abade|lang=sco}}, {{term|abaid||abode|lang=sco}}. For the change of vowel, compare ''abode'', preterit of ''abide''.

